21/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Meeting on Thursday (August 20th), the National Security Board approved a government initiative to expand the cultural rights of Turkey's Kurd minority.
The board includes military officers.
Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan recently launched the government initiative to end the 25-year-long Kurdish insurgency.
It includes restoring the names of Kurdish villages and possibly allowing sermons to be delivered in Kurdish.
(Hurriyet - 21/08/09;
Reuters - 20/08/09)
